<p>The thermal reduction of KMnO
 <sub>4</sub> has been reported by Kappestein [
 <xref rid="B20-nanomaterials-09-01156" ref-type="bibr">20</xref>] and Herbstein [
 <xref rid="B21-nanomaterials-09-01156" ref-type="bibr">21</xref>]. In the study conducted by Herbstein et al. [
 <xref rid="B21-nanomaterials-09-01156" ref-type="bibr">21</xref>] on the thermal decomposition of KMnO
 <sub>4</sub> in a temperature range of 25 to 900 °C, in an atmosphere of air and nitrogen, it was found that the idealized equation for the decomposition of KMnO
 <sub>4</sub> in air at 250 °C results in a soluble phase, the K
 <sub>2</sub>MnO
 <sub>4</sub>, and another phase that is insoluble, like this:
